</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-a7f7" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-dxcExB gjNMyZ pf-662_ pf-color-scheme-1 pf-lg-hide pf-md-hide pf-sm-hide"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-kqGpvY OSjcf"><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-661_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-lnPyOc gUmbDa pf-660_"><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-580_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-lnPyOc gUmbDa pf-579_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-brPMkR cnEYUf pf-537_ pf-heading-1-h3">Common challenges faced by health and social care managers</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Top_pain_points_in_CQC-regulated_services_and_how_to_solve_them_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.jpg?v=1727439145" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Top_pain_points_in_CQC-regulated_services_and_how_to_solve_them_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.jpg?v=1727439145 1536w" width="1348" height="899" alt="Top pain points in CQC-regulated services and how to solve them - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Top pain points in CQC-regulated services and how to solve them - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gdyfxU iluFjz pf-532_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-iMWBWc laPXAE pf-534_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by DC_Studio via Envato Elements</p><div class="sc-ifjxUM kHByph pf-578_ pf-icon-right" data-scroll-to-top="true" data-open-multiple="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3"><details class="sc-blFMWp dkcUcf pf-545_" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content.Wrapper"><summary><div class="sc-iUHVUy kMSpKC pf-538_ pf-anchor pf-header-item-wrapper" data-header-id="5f41b70e-85cf-474f-87bc-69b9174a0a00" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Header"><svg class="pf-accordion-icon pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow" style="width:auto;fill:currentcolor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 320 512"><path d="M278.6 233.4c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.8 0 45.3l-160 160c-12.5 12.5-32.8 12.5-45.3 0s-12.5-32.8 0-45.3L210.7 256 73.4 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.8 0-45.3s32.8-12.5 45.3 0l160 160z"></path></svg><span>Regulatory compliance - A constantly moving target</span></div></summary><div class="sc-cbekWb epYnlz pf-544_ pf-accordion-body" data-pf-expandable="true" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content"><div class="pf-accordion-display-content"><div data-pf-type="Accordion3.Flex.Content" class="sc-fGdjyZ edCvjl pf-543_"><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-542_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-lnPyOc gUmbDa pf-541_"><p class="sc-iMWBWc laPXAE pf-540_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">For many health and social care managers, keeping up with regulatory requirements is like trying to hit a moving target. CQC inspections, health and safety standards, safeguarding policies, and GDPR compliance are just a few of the many obligations that must be met. This regulatory burden can lead to a constant state of anxiety as managers worry about missing critical updates or failing to meet inspection standards. The pressure to remain compliant can detract from focusing on delivering high-quality care.
</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></details><details class="sc-blFMWp dkcUcf pf-553_" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content.Wrapper"><summary><div class="sc-iUHVUy kMSpKC pf-546_ pf-anchor pf-header-item-wrapper" data-header-id="c7bc69b9-174a-4a00-a2bf-1e424dd32f0e" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Header"><svg class="pf-accordion-icon pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow" style="width:auto;fill:currentcolor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 320 512"><path d="M278.6 233.4c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.8 0 45.3l-160 160c-12.5 12.5-32.8 12.5-45.3 0s-12.5-32.8 0-45.3L210.7 256 73.4 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.8 0-45.3s32.8-12.5 45.3 0l160 160z"></path></svg><span>Staffing issues - Finding and retaining talent</span></div></summary><div class="sc-cbekWb epYnlz pf-552_ pf-accordion-body" data-pf-expandable="true" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content"><div class="pf-accordion-display-content"><div data-pf-type="Accordion3.Flex.Content" class="sc-fGdjyZ edCvjl pf-551_"><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-550_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-lnPyOc gUmbDa pf-549_"><p class="sc-iMWBWc laPXAE pf-548_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Recruitment and retention are perennial challenges in the health and social care sector. High turnover rates, staff burnout, and difficulties attracting qualified professionals can leave managers scrambling to fill gaps. This puts a strain on the remaining staff and can compromise the quality and consistency of care provided. Furthermore, the time and resources spent on continuous recruitment and training can significantly drain the organisation.
</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></details><details class="sc-blFMWp dkcUcf pf-561_" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content.Wrapper"><summary><div class="sc-iUHVUy kMSpKC pf-554_ pf-anchor pf-header-item-wrapper" data-header-id="22bf1e42-4dd3-4f0e-a948-d3844c3addec" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Header"><svg class="pf-accordion-icon pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow" style="width:auto;fill:currentcolor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 320 512"><path d="M278.6 233.4c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.8 0 45.3l-160 160c-12.5 12.5-32.8 12.5-45.3 0s-12.5-32.8 0-45.3L210.7 256 73.4 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.8 0-45.3s32.8-12.5 45.3 0l160 160z"></path></svg><span>Financial constraints - Balancing quality and sustainability</span></div></summary><div class="sc-cbekWb epYnlz pf-560_ pf-accordion-body" data-pf-expandable="true" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content"><div class="pf-accordion-display-content"><div data-pf-type="Accordion3.Flex.Content" class="sc-fGdjyZ edCvjl pf-559_"><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-558_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-lnPyOc gUmbDa pf-557_"><p class="sc-iMWBWc laPXAE pf-556_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Budgetary constraints are a reality for most health and social care providers. With increasing operational costs and limited funding, managers often find themselves making tough decisions that can impact service quality. Whether it’s investing in staff training, upgrading facilities, or implementing new technology, finding the balance between delivering high-quality care and maintaining financial sustainability is a delicate act.
</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></details><details class="sc-blFMWp dkcUcf pf-569_" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content.Wrapper"><summary><div class="sc-iUHVUy kMSpKC pf-562_ pf-anchor pf-header-item-wrapper" data-header-id="a948d384-4c3a-4dec-8d62-956c23361c9b" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Header"><svg class="pf-accordion-icon pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow" style="width:auto;fill:currentcolor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 320 512"><path d="M278.6 233.4c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.8 0 45.3l-160 160c-12.5 12.5-32.8 12.5-45.3 0s-12.5-32.8 0-45.3L210.7 256 73.4 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.8 0-45.3s32.8-12.5 45.3 0l160 160z"></path></svg><span>Meeting patient and service user expectations</span></div></summary><div class="sc-cbekWb epYnlz pf-568_ pf-accordion-body" data-pf-expandable="true" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content"><div class="pf-accordion-display-content"><div data-pf-type="Accordion3.Flex.Content" class="sc-fGdjyZ edCvjl pf-567_"><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-566_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-lnPyOc gUmbDa pf-565_"><p class="sc-iMWBWc laPXAE pf-564_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">As the population becomes more informed and health-conscious, expectations for personalised, high-quality care have risen. Managers are under constant pressure to not only meet but exceed these expectations while adhering to strict regulatory standards. Complaints and negative feedback can quickly spiral into significant challenges, impacting staff morale and the reputation of the service.
</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></details><details class="sc-blFMWp dkcUcf pf-577_" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content.Wrapper"><summary><div class="sc-iUHVUy kMSpKC pf-570_ pf-anchor pf-header-item-wrapper" data-header-id="4d62956c-2336-4c9b-85ea-a05df5ca8601" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Header"><svg class="pf-accordion-icon pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow" style="width:auto;fill:currentcolor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 320 512"><path d="M278.6 233.4c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.8 0 45.3l-160 160c-12.5 12.5-32.8 12.5-45.3 0s-12.5-32.8 0-45.3L210.7 256 73.4 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.8 0-45.3s32.8-12.5 45.3 0l160 160z"></path></svg><span>Embracing technology - A double-edged sword</span></div></summary><div class="sc-cbekWb epYnlz pf-576_ pf-accordion-body" data-pf-expandable="true" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content"><div class="pf-accordion-display-content"><div data-pf-type="Accordion3.Flex.Content" class="sc-fGdjyZ edCvjl pf-575_"><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-574_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-lnPyOc gUmbDa pf-573_"><p class="sc-iMWBWc laPXAE pf-572_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Digital solutions can significantly improve service delivery and efficiency, but their implementation is often met with resistance. Managers must navigate the complexities of integrating new systems with existing workflows, ensuring data security and training staff to use these tools effectively. For many, the prospect of another technological upheaval is daunting, despite the potential benefits.
</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></details></div></div></div></div><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-590_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-lnPyOc gUmbDa pf-585_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-brPMkR cnEYUf pf-582_ pf-heading-1-h3">The impact of these challenges</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/CQC-regulated_services_Common_challenges_and_practical_solutions_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.jpg?v=1727439143" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/CQC-regulated_services_Common_challenges_and_practical_solutions_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.jpg?v=1727439143 1536w" width="1933" height="1290" alt="CQC-regulated services: Common challenges and practical solutions - Dr Richard Dune -" title="CQC-regulated services: Common challenges and practical solutions - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gdyfxU iluFjz pf-586_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-iMWBWc laPXAE pf-588_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by shotprime via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-iMWBWc laPXAE pf-584_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">These common challenges have far-reaching consequences for health and social care services. Struggling to maintain compliance can lead to regulatory actions, financial penalties, or even closure. Staffing shortages can compromise care quality and lead to staff burnout, increasing turnover rates further. Financial difficulties can restrict growth and innovation, while unmet patient expectations can damage the service’s reputation and erode trust.
<br><br>In the face of these pressures, it is unsurprising that many managers feel overwhelmed. The constant juggling of responsibilities, coupled with the high stakes involved, can lead to stress and burnout for those at the helm. So, what can be done to alleviate these burdens and improve service delivery?
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-639_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-lnPyOc gUmbDa pf-638_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-brPMkR cnEYUf pf-596_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommendations for overcoming common challenges</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Pain_points_in_CQC_compliance_Key_solutions_for_service_managers_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.jpg?v=1727439144" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Pain_points_in_CQC_compliance_Key_solutions_for_service_managers_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.jpg?v=1727439144 1536w" width="1890" height="1260" alt="Pain points in CQC compliance: Key solutions for service managers - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Pain points in CQC compliance: Key solutions for service managers - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gdyfxU iluFjz pf-591_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-iMWBWc laPXAE pf-593_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by DragonImages via Envato Elements</p><div class="sc-ifjxUM kHByph pf-637_ pf-icon-right" data-scroll-to-top="true" data-open-multiple="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3"><details class="sc-blFMWp dkcUcf pf-604_" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content.Wrapper"><summary><div class="sc-iUHVUy kMSpKC pf-597_ pf-anchor pf-header-item-wrapper" data-header-id="64d53bff-e2fe-4676-9a67-ab0d78e02749" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Header"><svg class="pf-accordion-icon pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow" style="width:auto;fill:currentcolor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 320 512"><path d="M278.6 233.4c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.8 0 45.3l-160 160c-12.5 12.5-32.8 12.5-45.3 0s-12.5-32.8 0-45.3L210.7 256 73.4 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.8 0-45.3s32.8-12.5 45.3 0l160 160z"></path></svg><span>Streamline compliance management with digital solutions</span></div></summary><div class="sc-cbekWb epYnlz pf-603_ pf-accordion-body" data-pf-expandable="true" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content"><div class="pf-accordion-display-content"><div data-pf-type="Accordion3.Flex.Content" class="sc-fGdjyZ edCvjl pf-602_"><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-601_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-lnPyOc gUmbDa pf-600_"><p class="sc-iMWBWc laPXAE pf-599_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Utilising comprehensive compliance management software like ComplyPlus™ can significantly reduce the administrative burden associated with regulatory compliance. Managers can ensure that their service remains compliant without the constant need for manual oversight by automating processes such as policy updates, training reminders, and audit trails.
</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></details><details class="sc-blFMWp dkcUcf pf-612_" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content.Wrapper"><summary><div class="sc-iUHVUy kMSpKC pf-605_ pf-anchor pf-header-item-wrapper" data-header-id="9a67ab0d-78e0-4749-8654-e247c55ccf31" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Header"><svg class="pf-accordion-icon pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow" style="width:auto;fill:currentcolor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 320 512"><path d="M278.6 233.4c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.8 0 45.3l-160 160c-12.5 12.5-32.8 12.5-45.3 0s-12.5-32.8 0-45.3L210.7 256 73.4 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.8 0-45.3s32.8-12.5 45.3 0l160 160z"></path></svg><span>Invest in workforce development and retention</span></div></summary><div class="sc-cbekWb epYnlz pf-611_ pf-accordion-body" data-pf-expandable="true" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content"><div class="pf-accordion-display-content"><div data-pf-type="Accordion3.Flex.Content" class="sc-fGdjyZ edCvjl pf-610_"><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-609_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-lnPyOc gUmbDa pf-608_"><p class="sc-iMWBWc laPXAE pf-607_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Creating a supportive and empowering environment for staff is crucial for retention. Offering regular training and development opportunities enhances skills and boosts morale and job satisfaction. Structured career development plans and wellbeing initiatives can further reduce turnover and attract high-quality candidates.
</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></details><details class="sc-blFMWp dkcUcf pf-620_" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content.Wrapper"><summary><div class="sc-iUHVUy kMSpKC pf-613_ pf-anchor pf-header-item-wrapper" data-header-id="0654e247-c55c-4f31-856e-8fd16a57ba4c" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Header"><svg class="pf-accordion-icon pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow" style="width:auto;fill:currentcolor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 320 512"><path d="M278.6 233.4c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.8 0 45.3l-160 160c-12.5 12.5-32.8 12.5-45.3 0s-12.5-32.8 0-45.3L210.7 256 73.4 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.8 0-45.3s32.8-12.5 45.3 0l160 160z"></path></svg><span>Implement strategic financial planning</span></div></summary><div class="sc-cbekWb epYnlz pf-619_ pf-accordion-body" data-pf-expandable="true" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content"><div class="pf-accordion-display-content"><div data-pf-type="Accordion3.Flex.Content" class="sc-fGdjyZ edCvjl pf-618_"><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-617_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-lnPyOc gUmbDa pf-616_"><p class="sc-iMWBWc laPXAE pf-615_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Proactive financial planning and management are essential for sustaining high-quality service delivery. This includes exploring funding opportunities, optimising resource allocation, and investing in cost-effective solutions like digital tools that can streamline operations and reduce long-term costs.
</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></details><details class="sc-blFMWp dkcUcf pf-628_" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content.Wrapper"><summary><div class="sc-iUHVUy kMSpKC pf-621_ pf-anchor pf-header-item-wrapper" data-header-id="c56e8fd1-6a57-4a4c-89bf-ea32e46f6931" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Header"><svg class="pf-accordion-icon pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow" style="width:auto;fill:currentcolor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 320 512"><path d="M278.6 233.4c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.8 0 45.3l-160 160c-12.5 12.5-32.8 12.5-45.3 0s-12.5-32.8 0-45.3L210.7 256 73.4 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.8 0-45.3s32.8-12.5 45.3 0l160 160z"></path></svg><span>Enhance communication and engagement with service users</span></div></summary><div class="sc-cbekWb epYnlz pf-627_ pf-accordion-body" data-pf-expandable="true" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content"><div class="pf-accordion-display-content"><div data-pf-type="Accordion3.Flex.Content" class="sc-fGdjyZ edCvjl pf-626_"><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-625_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-lnPyOc gUmbDa pf-624_"><p class="sc-iMWBWc laPXAE pf-623_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Building strong relationships with service users through regular communication and feedback can help manage expectations and improve satisfaction. Implementing training programmes focused on person-centred care and communication can empower staff to engage effectively with service users, leading to improved outcomes and reduced complaints.
</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></details><details class="sc-blFMWp dkcUcf pf-636_" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content.Wrapper"><summary><div class="sc-iUHVUy kMSpKC pf-629_ pf-anchor pf-header-item-wrapper" data-header-id="49bfea32-e46f-4931-855e-1314ebc8f0d4" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Header"><svg class="pf-accordion-icon pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow" style="width:auto;fill:currentcolor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 320 512"><path d="M278.6 233.4c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.8 0 45.3l-160 160c-12.5 12.5-32.8 12.5-45.3 0s-12.5-32.8 0-45.3L210.7 256 73.4 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.8 0-45.3s32.8-12.5 45.3 0l160 160z"></path></svg><span>Embrace technology with a strategic approach</span></div></summary><div class="sc-cbekWb epYnlz pf-635_ pf-accordion-body" data-pf-expandable="true" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content"><div class="pf-accordion-display-content"><div data-pf-type="Accordion3.Flex.Content" class="sc-fGdjyZ edCvjl pf-634_"><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-633_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-lnPyOc gUmbDa pf-632_"><p class="sc-iMWBWc laPXAE pf-631_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">While technology can be transformative, it’s essential to approach its implementation thoughtfully. Conducting a needs assessment, involving staff in decision-making, and providing comprehensive training can ease the transition and maximise the benefits of new systems.
